    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1923-06-25T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1923-06-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="10"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d10">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.5112/72a</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        French Ambassador</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Jusserand</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-06-25">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 25, 1923</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Ambassador</hi>: Permit me to enclose in
                    further response to your suggestion of yesterday, a draft of a proposed
                    agreement for the renewal of the Arbitration Treaty with France.<note n="20"
                        xml:id="d10fn20">Enclosure not printed.</note> This <pb facs="0138" n="14"
                        xml:id="pg_14"/> is similar to the agreement which was signed on Saturday
                    with Great Britain when the notes to which I referred in my first letter today
                    were exchanged.</p>
                <p>Very sincerely yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Charles E. Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
